From: Barry <barry@curran.co>
Date: 2026-05-14
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] EFMesh: default canned/invite message

Replaces the upstream Arizona-Meshtastic-Community default canned
message with the Electric Forest Meshtastic Community invite. The
AmbassadorModule sends this string (prefixed with "Hello <shortname>, ")
as a direct message to any newly-discovered node.

EFMesh is NOT officially endorsed by Electric Forest. EFMesh is a
community-run Meshtastic mesh organized around Electric Forest
attendees.

--- a/src/modules/CannedMessageModule.cpp
+++ b/src/modules/CannedMessageModule.cpp
@@ -2301,7 +2301,7 @@
 void CannedMessageModule::installDefaultCannedMessageModuleConfig()
 {
-    const char *defaultMessages = "I'd like to invite you to join the Arizona Meshtastic Community (azmsh.net) over on MediumFast Slot 18";
+    const char *defaultMessages = "Hello! I'd like to invite you to join the Electric Forest Meshtastic Community (efmesh.com) over on MediumFast preset.";
     strncpy(cannedMessageModuleConfig.messages, defaultMessages, sizeof(cannedMessageModuleConfig.messages));
 }
